skow.jpeg 750w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:786/1*whiRX1o_7J3jkxB5Ljskow.jpeg 786w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:828/1*whiRX1o_7J3jkxB5Ljskow.jpeg 828w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1100/1*whiRX1o_7J3jkxB5Ljskow.jpeg 1100w, https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*whiRX1o_7J3jkxB5Ljskow.jpeg 1400w"/><img alt="" loading="lazy" role="presentation" src="https://miro.medium.com/max/700/1*whiRX1o_7J3jkxB5Ljskow.jpeg"></picture></div><p class="mbr-description mbr-fonts-style mt-2 align-center display-12 text-muted" style="font-size:12px;">DeepChem and Andreessen Horowitz want to eat the world of AI for chemistry, by using technology lock-in.</p><br></div></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="content5 cid-tt5UseJ9wk" id="content5-4" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px;background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">While MoleculeNet team members avoided to benchmark char-CNN, they still found time to design fancy landing pages for MoleculeNet and DeepChem, which suggests that their <strong>priority is PR fluff,</strong> and not solid science. It’s a strategy typical in the Silicon Valley, where startups design <strong>mock products</strong> to attract traffic, and then rely on their community to build the real thing.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
